From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 23:58:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: ignore empty Fruit Jam usbhost RX EOP events

The gated GET_DESCRIPTOR probe can see RX_START/RX_EOP with no decoded bytes
immediately after host TX.  Treat that as a timing artifact from the host EOP
window, clear the receive IRQs, and keep waiting for a real device packet.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -1204 +1204,10 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_receive_raw(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh, bool ack_data
+			if (!len) {
+				/*
+				 * Gated receive can start in the host EOP window:
+				 * ignore the empty event and keep waiting for the
+				 * device response packet.
+				 */
+				writel(FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_ALL, uh->pio + FJ_PIO_IRQ);
+				continue;
+			}
 			ret = len ? 0 : -ENODATA;
-- 
